				\begin{document}$$23\,^{\circ }$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M24"><mml:mrow><mml:mn>23</mml:mn><mml:msup><mml:mspace width="0.166667em"/><mml:mo>&#x02218;</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="11538_2017_350_Article_IEq12.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>C. Following planting to the imaging assays, plants were grown for 14 days in a growth chamber (Fitotron SGR; Weiss Gallenkamp, Loughborough, UK). The rhizosphere chambers were kept hydrated via capillary rise, at a water potential of <inline-formula id="IEq13"><alternatives><tex-math id="M25">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
